      // §01 Bio
      section(class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-12 py-16 md:py-20")
        h2(class="font-mono text-xs uppercase text-muted-fg mb-10 flex items-center gap-4", style="letter-spacing:0.2em")
          span §01
          span Bio
        div(class="max-w-3xl space-y-6 font-serif text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed")
          p
            | Dr.-Ing. Fabian Schuh is a blockchain engineer and entrepreneur based in Buckenhof, Germany.
            | He is the founder and CEO of #[a(class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:bg-ink hover:text-paper transition-colors duration-100", href="https://chainsquad.com") ChainSquad GmbH],
            | a technology consultancy delivering Web2 and Web3 infrastructure since 2016.
            | He holds a PhD in communications engineering from Friedrich-Alexander-Universität Erlangen-Nürnberg,
            | where his research focused on digital communications, low-latency transmission, and constant-envelope signalling.
          p
            | His blockchain work began in the Graphene era: as a founding member of Cryptonomex Inc. he wrote the
            | full-featured Python libraries for BitShares, Steem, Peerplays, and the underlying
            | #[code graphenelib]. He led Python development and advisory work at Steemit Inc., built Streemian.com
            | as a solo MicroSaaS (later acquired), and contributed to early DAO governance and escrow systems on
            | BitShares — including being among the first people hired and paid directly by a blockchain.
          p
            | Since 2023 his focus has shifted to the Solana ecosystem. He ships recurring-payment infrastructure at
            | #[a(class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:bg-ink hover:text-paper transition-colors duration-100", href="https://tributary.so") tributary.so],
            | prediction-market and betting rails at
            | #[a(class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:bg-ink hover:text-paper transition-colors duration-100", href="https://mash.fun") mash.fun]
            | and DeFi tooling through Lucky Swaps. He is a Colosseum hackathon winner, a Solana Security #2 graduate, and a SuperteamDE member.
          p
            | The current chapter is AI agents: multi-agent software-development automation at
            | #[a(class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:bg-ink hover:text-paper transition-colors duration-100", href="https://chaoscraft.dev") chaoscraft.dev]
            | and Polycode, agent-friendly payment primitives (lando,
            | #[a(class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:bg-ink hover:text-paper transition-colors duration-100", href="https://allowly.app") allowly.app]),
            | and onchain agent tooling — most recently recognised at the 2026 Colosseum Frontier hackathon for building an autonomous onchain agent with the Zerion CLI.

